yingyinNormal.en: Did you know? In 1980, the Chinese were the 10th-largest immigrant group in the U.S..
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道吗？在1980年，中华民族是美国第10大移民种族。

yingyinNormal.en: Sam Nguyen was my high school janitor. He was an immigrant from Vietnam who barely spoke a word of English.
yingyinNormal.zh: 山姆·阮是我高中里的保卫人员，他是越南移民，他几乎不说英语。

yingyinNormal.en: Is it worth our time? I'm not sure this guy can pay. He's an undocumented immigrant. He owns a body shop.
yingyinNormal.zh: 值得付出时间吗？恐怕他付不起，他是无证移民，开了一家汽车维修店。

yingyinNormal.en: It's not about you. It's about a poor immigrant from Pakistan trying to make his way in America by working the graveyard shift at the Colorado Boulevard Chevron.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这不是你想不想的问题，这关系到可怜的巴基斯坦移民在科罗拉多大道的雪佛龙公司上夜班，就为了在美国混口饭吃。

yingyinNormal.en: And I had no idea that something I did could mean more than ever imagined to an immigrant from Vietnam who barely even spoke English.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我以前不知道我所做的对于一个几乎不说英语的越南人能发挥如此超乎我想象的作用。
